[ kopiwm ]
------------
kopiwm is a small dynamic window manager for X.


Requirements
------------
In order to build kopiwm you need the Xlib header files, and the Zig
compiler.


Installation
------------
Enter the following command to build and install kopiwm (if necessary
as root):

    zig build --prefix /usr/local -Doptimize=ReleaseFast install


Running kopiwm
--------------
Add the following line to your .xinitrc to start kopiwm using startx:

    exec kopiwm

In order to connect kopiwm to a specific display, make sure that
the DISPLAY environment variable is set correctly, e.g.:

    DISPLAY=foo.bar:1 exec kopiwm

(This will start kopiwm on display :1 of the host foo.bar.)

In order to display status info in the bar, you can do something
like this in your .xinitrc:

    while xsetroot -name "`date` `uptime | sed 's/.*,//'`"
    do
    	sleep 1
    done &
    exec kopiwm


Configuration
-------------
The configuration of kopiwm is done by editing ./src/config.zig and
(re)compiling the source code.
